headline: Humana (NYSE:HUM) Posts Q1 Sales In Line With Estimates, Stock Soars
summary: Health insurance company Humana (NYSE:HUM) met Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q1 CY2025, with sales up 8.4% year on year to $32.11 billion. The company’s full-year revenue guidance of $127 billion at the midpoint came in 0.7% above analysts’ estimates. Its GAAP profit of $10.30 per share was 3.4% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
